Package RUClinic

package RUClinic
  • Class
    Description
    Appointment
    The Appointment class is used to create appointments in the clinic that contain the date and time of the appointment, the name of the patient and the name of the provider that is being seen.
    CircularlyLinkedList
    This class is solely for maintaining the technicians in a circular linked list
    ClinicManager
    The ClinicManager class is used for processing input commands from the terminal It allows for users to manage and interact with the clinic
    Date
    The Date class is used to hold a date with the variables: year, month, and day.
    DateTest
    This Junit class is used to test the isValid() method for the Date class to ensure that it works
    Doctor
    The Doctor class defines the specialty and unique npi number of the provider It is a subclass of the Provider class
    Imaging
    The Imaging class represents an imaging appointment in the clinic.
    List<E>
    A generic List class that stores elements of type E in a linear data structure
    ListTest
     
    Location
    The Location class keeps track of all the clinic locations via the location's name, county, and zip code.
    Patient
    The Patient class defines a person as a patient and keeps track of their profile and the visits they made to the providers in our scheduler It is a subclass of the superclass Person
    Person
    The Person class is the superclass of the Patient and Provider class It is the basis for all people in the clinic
    Profile
    The Profile class manages the profiles of all people in the clinic, including their fname, lname, and date of birth This class serves as a neater and more efficient way of managing/maintaining peoples' information
    ProfileTest
    This Junit class is used to test the compareTo() method for the Profile class to ensure that it works
    Provider
    The Provider class defines a person as a provider and keeps track of their profile and their practice location It is a subclass of the superclass Person but also the superclass of the Doctor and the Technician class
    Radiology
    The Radiology class represents a radiology room that provides imaging services
    Radiology.ImagingService
    Simple enum type that represents the types of imaging services in the clinic
    RunProject2
    The Driver class for the clinic, runs the ClinicManager class via the run method
    Sort
    The Sort class handles all the sorting done for the lists of people in the clinic
    Specialty
    The Specialty class defines and maintains the certain specialties the providers have which determines how much they charge patients per visit
    Technician
    The Technician class defines the unique charging rate for each technician It is a subclass of the Provider class.
    Timeslot
     
    Visit
    The Visit class is used to define a node in a singly linked list that maintains the list of visits in the clinic.
